2.10	Calcot,_Berkshire	Calcot, Berkshire	Calcot, or Calcot Row, is a suburb west of Reading in the English county of Berkshire. Calcot is situated along the A4 Bath Road between the old hamlet of Horncastle and Junction 12 of the M4 motorway. The suburb of Tilehurst lies to the north and in the hills above Calcot, while the village of Theale lies to the west across the motorway. The recent housing estates of Beansheaf Farm and Fords Farm lie to the south, and may be considered part of Calcot.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b0/Calcot_mansion.jpg/240px-Calcot_mansion.jpg
